                    <note>
                        
                        <ab type="history">The chronicle of King <persName ref="PRS4428Galawdew"/> locates ʾAraftā somewhere in <placeName ref="LOC6569Tegray"/>. 
                            According to this chronicle, it was a place where the Christians army became victorious over the Muslims forces with the support of the <placeName ref="LOC5111Portug"/>
                            soldiers in<date>1542</date>. On the other hand, <persName ref="PRS3047Castanho"/>'s account reports the Portuguese army defeated the forces of 
                            <persName ref="PRS1500Ahmad"/> in the same year, as indicated in the chronicle, at a place called <placeName ref="LOC1400AmbaSa"/> which is today in the region of 
                            <placeName ref="LOC1263Adwa"/>. <placeName ref="LOC1400AmbaSa"/> has 70 districts. Therefore, ʾAraftā would probably be a locality in one of the districts of <placeName ref="LOC1400AmbaSa"/>. </ab> 
               
                        
                        
